Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle of a probably Pamphylian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Similar stamps, but not as this, in C. Brixhe, Timbres amphoriques de Pamphylie (Paris 2012). Name Eurukrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0076)
